CEZ, Akkok Get About 20 Bidders for Akenerji Sale, Vatan Reports

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-05-23T08:25:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/cez-akkok-get-about-20-bidders-for-akenerji-sale-vatan-reports.html
Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR) , a
Turkish utility owned by the Czech Republic’s  CEZ AS (CEZ)  and
Turkey’s Akkok Group, got more than 20 potential bidders for
their stakes in the company,  Vatan  reported, citing Akkok chief
executive Mehmet Ali Berkman.  CEZ and Akkok each own 37.5 percent of Akenerji, the
Istanbul-based newspaper reported. The remaining 25 percent is
traded on the Istanbul stock exchange. Berkman didn’t name any
of the companies that might bid, Vatan said.  Norway’s Statkraft SF as well as Enerjisa, a joint venture
between Turkey’s  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  and  Verbund AG (VER) ,
Limak Yatirim Holding,  Turcas Petrol AS (TRCAS)  and Borusan Holding are
among the companies interested in the sale, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 